{"key":"processedPost-11655272","value":{"id":11655272,"first":11655218,"last":11688163,"when":1260906635,"utime":"12/15/09 09:50 PM","cleanedPost":"I've not noticed a difference in hardwoods.&nbsp; Every area of the world has it's own local tree population, and they all seem to work.<br />I wouldn't let the tubes solidify in the PC.&nbsp; The lids need to be tightened after removal while hot, regardless if you tighten them before the PC cycle or not.&nbsp; They always seem to work loose.&nbsp; I let them solidify in front of a flow hood as shown below.&nbsp; If you're doing something else and don't have a rack, you could make one out of clothes hangers or other stiff wire.<br />RR<br /><a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/07-009/285547682-Test_Tube_rack_at_slant_2a.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/07-009/285547682-thumb_Test_Tube_rack_at_slant_2a.jpg\"></a>"}}